Endpoints are open to abuse/brute-force. Add `express-rate-limit`:
```js
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, max: 100 }));
```

**4. No global error handler**
If any middleware or route throws, Express will return a default error page that can leak stack traces in development. Add a global error handler:
```js
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.message);
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});
